      "description": "Available is a museum-grade 2008 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the S65B40 4.0L naturally aspirated V8, a high-revving masterpiece with an 8,400 RPM redline and individual throttle bodies. This specimen is equipped with a crisp 6-speed manual gearbox and the GKN-sourced M Variable Differential Lock for optimal torque vectoring. The chassis is equipped with Electronic Damper Control (EDC), providing exceptional lateral stability and damping precision. Preventative maintenance is comprehensive, including recent rod bearing replacement with VAC-coated shells and ARP hardware to ensure long-term mechanical integrity. The exterior finish and interior upholstery are in showroom condition, free of common wear on the seat bolsters or UV degradation on the carbon fiber roof. This is a turnkey, collector-quality example for the most demanding purist.",
